comments.body:
@amykang2020 how does the entrypoint script looks like?  You need to ensure two things:

- the mounted cgroup is writeable at any level (either run privileged or `--security-opt=unmask=/sys/fs/cgroup`)
- all the processes are in a leaf node cgroup, so it means you need to create a sub-cgroup as part of the entrypoint to your container and then move all the processes in the container there.  This is a requirement with cgroup2 as procosses can be only in the leaf nodes.
